(5. As per the Trust Deed \(Clause 9\(a\)\), trustees other than the hereditary) Tj T*
(   trustee are to be appointed by the District Court for 5 years after) Tj T*
(   consulting the Charity Commissioner. The Deed mandates that an) Tj T*
(   application for new trustee appointment must be filed with the District) Tj T*
(   Court at least 3 months before the term expires, i.e., by 12/06/2024.) Tj T*
(   The current trustees failed to file any such application at the Sessions) Tj T*
(   Court, Bhiwandi.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(6. Instead, three trustees - Shri Madhukar Patkar, Shri Dhanesh Gosavi,) Tj T*
(   and Shri Milind Chorghe - filed Miscellaneous Application No. 44/2024) Tj T*
(   at the Sessions Court, Bhiwandi, seeking extension of their term. This) Tj T*
(   is contrary to the Trust Deed, which contains no such provision. Since) Tj T*
(   the Charity Commissioner has been made a Respondent in that application,) Tj T*
(   we request that an objection be filed opposing the extension.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(--- PROPERTY AND INCOME OF THE SANSTHAN ---) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(7. Shrimant Chimaji Appa donated 6 villages to Shri Vajreshwari Devi in) Tj T*
(   1738 after the capture of Vasai Fort. The British Government continued) Tj T*
(   the grant and issued Sanads for the following villages:) Tj T*
(   - Moje Vajreshwari, Taluka Bhiwandi        - Sanad No. 77, dated 09/10/1884) Tj T*
(   - Kaap Kaneri village                      - Sanad No. 74, dated 14/07/1864) Tj T*
(   - Phene village                            - Sanad No. 73, dated 14/07/1864) Tj T*
(   - Moje Bhinar, Taluka Vasai                - Sanad No. 87, dated 20/03/1885) Tj T*
(   - Vadghar village                          - Sanad No. 85, dated 04/10/1884) Tj T*
(   - Ambode village                           - Sanad No. 86, dated 10/03/1885) Tj T*
(   Total land: approximately 3,000 acres \(Inam Class 3\).) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(8. Income sources include: land rent/lease from inam lands, donations,) Tj T*
(   offerings, fixed deposit interest, and various religious contributions.) Tj T*
(   Annual income is approximately Rs. 2 Crores.) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(--- ALLEGATIONS OF MISCONDUCT BY CURRENT TRUSTEES ---) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(ALLEGATION 12\(1\) - MISAPPROPRIATION OF GOLD AND SILVER ORNAMENTS:) Tj T*
() Tj T*
(When the current trustees took charge, an inventory of valuables was taken.) Tj T*
(During an inspection on 07/07/2022 in the presence of the Inspector, the) Tj T*
(following serious irregularities were found:) Tj T*
(- Approximately 40 tolas \(approx. 466 grams\) of gold found missing.) Tj T*
(- In a necklace of 19 gold figurines: 3 figurines were found to be silver.) Tj T*
(- In a necklace of 17 gold figurines: 4 figurines were found to be silver.) Tj T*
(- In a necklace of 18 gold figurines: 5 figurines were found to be silver.) Tj T*
(- Out of gold beads \(parachhuran\): 19 beads and 1 nose ring found fake.) Tj T*
ET
